i### Leaving VSCode	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iBecause it's a RAM-hungry graphics application. You shouldn't	/	tilde.team	70
ineed that much memory to edit text and connect to an LSP	/	tilde.team	70
iserver. We're talking about 1.2 GB compared with around 200	/	tilde.team	70
iMB for the same project.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iAlso, I don't want all the additional features offered, such	/	tilde.team	70
ias file name and text parsing, to suggest that I download	/	tilde.team	70
iextensions. I simply need a simple, functional text-editing	/	tilde.team	70
iapplication. I don't enjoy using VSCode anymore, so it's	/	tilde.team	70
itime to say goodbye.	/	tilde.team	70
hVSCode	URL:https://code.visualstudio.com/	code.visualstudio.com	443
i	/	tilde.team	70
i### Choosing Emacs	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
